Minister Mosebenzi Zwane says they are addressing the lack of support for young people wishing to enter the mining sector. CAPE TOWN - Mineral Resources Minister Mosebenzi Zwane says they are addressing the lack of support for young people wishing to enter the mining sector.Zwane addressed delegates on the last day of the Mining Indaba in Cape Town earlier on Thursday.The minister says that young people are hampered from entering the mining sector due to a lack of support and funding. In this regard, we help by linking potential and sustainable projects with financial institutions or investors. Deputy Minister in the Presidency Buti Manamela has called on private mining companies to transform the industry to attract more interest from young people. If we begin to say to young people we re talking quality jobs and pay, and you owning and controlling the biggest stake within the mining sector, then you ll get their attention (sic). Manamela says mining corporates need to be involved in education and skills development in mining communities.#MiningIndaba Minister Buti Manamela: How do we link mining activities to sustainable livelihoods? IM(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)